# No commercial references in Cloud Foundry OSS docs

This is the **open-source Cloud Foundry** documentation set. Content must not reference commercial products, commercial product names, or commercial release version numbers.

## Prohibited terms → required replacements

| Prohibited | Use instead |
|------------|-------------|
| Tanzu (as product name) | Cloud Foundry |
| Tanzu Application Service / TAS | Cloud Foundry |
| TAS for VMs | Cloud Foundry |
| Tanzu Platform for Cloud Foundry | Cloud Foundry |
| Elastic Application Runtime | Cloud Foundry |
| Tanzu cf CLI | cf CLI |
| Tanzu UAA | UAA |
| Tanzu User Account and Authentication | User Account and Authentication (UAA) |
| VMware (in product context) | _(remove or rewrite)_ |
| Broadcom Support Portal / Tanzu Support Hub | _(remove link)_ |
| Extended App Support tile / Ops Manager tile | _(remove entirely — commercial TAS feature)_ |
| Commercial release versions: 2.x, 3.x, 4.x, 5.x, 6.0, 10.x | _(remove or rewrite without product version)_ |

## Acceptable

- Component/dependency version numbers: `cflinuxfs4 v1.45.0`, `cf CLI v8.12.0`.
- Infrastructure platform names as deployment targets: `VMware vSphere`, `AWS`, `GCP`, `Azure`, `OpenStack`.
- Links to open-source projects and GitHub repos.
- Content inside `<% if vars.platform_code == 'PCF' %>` blocks does **not** render in OSS builds and may remain.

## Verification

Before committing content changes, search across all content repos:

```
rg "Tanzu|TAS for VMs|Tanzu Application Service|Elastic Application Runtime|Tanzu Support Hub" --glob "*.html.md.erb" --glob "!archive/*"
```

Fix any hits that are not inside `<% if vars.platform_code == 'PCF' %>` guards.
